output.map_title: Map to show the number of graduates of Medicine and dentistry now working in Education who are currently living in each region five years after graduation, male and female first degree graduates from English HE providers, 2021/22 tax year.
output.maptext: For first degree graduates of Medicine and dentistry in the Education industry five years after graduation, the region where the most graduates had studied was London. The regions where the fewest graduates had studied were East Midlands and North East. The region where the highest number of graduates lived five years after graduation was London and the regions where the fewest graduates lived were East Midlands, East of England, North East, South East, West Midlands and Yorkshire and the Humber.
output.maptext2: For first degree graduates of Medicine and dentistry in the Education industry, the region with the smallest proportionate decrease in graduates who studied compared to living in the region five years after graduation was London, where the number of graduates decreased by -25%. The regions with the largest decrease were East of England, South East, West Midlands and Yorkshire and the Humber where the number of graduates decreased by -100%.
